g vote that drew Trump’s ire. </description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/indiana-republicans-lost-jobs-bucking-trump-zero-regrets-rcna343899</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/indiana-republicans-lost-jobs-bucking-trump-zero-regrets-rcna343899</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Sen-Greg-Walker-gk-bd3216.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Christine Tannous/IndyStar</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Indiana state Sen. Greg Walker, recites the Pledge of Allegiance</media:text><media:description type="plain">Indiana state Sen. Greg Walker, recites the Pledge of Allegiance on Tuesday, Nov. 18, 2025, during Org Day, the ceremonial first day of the 2026 legislative session, at the Indiana Statehouse in Indianapolis.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-sen-james-buck-gk-836468.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Grace Smith/IndyStar</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Indiana state Sen. Jim Buck, R-Kokomo, gives a concession speech Tuesday, May 5, 2026, during Howard County GOP&#39;s election night</media:text><media:description type="plain">Indiana state Sen. Jim Buck gives a concession speech in Kokomo after having lost his primary Tuesday.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-12/251212-Indiana-Statehouse-ew-426p-0af9de.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Kaiti Sullivan</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Indiana Senate Votes Down Trump-Backed Congressional Map</media:text><media:description type="plain">Republicans hoped a new congressional map in Indiana would have given them control over all nine districts.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Sen-Greg-Walker-gk-bd3216.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 23:51:31 GMT</pubDate><title>Indiana Republicans who lost their jobs after bucking Trump have ‘zero regrets’</title><updateDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 23:51:31 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Bridget Bowman</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Ben Kamisar</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Stephen Pettigrew</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 06 May 2026 02:51:49 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Democrat Chedrick Greene has won a special state Senate election in Michigan, NBC News projects, ensuring his party will keep control of the closely divided chamber in a key battleground state</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/democrats-keep-control-michigan-state-senate-special-election-win-rcna343690</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/democrats-keep-control-michigan-state-senate-special-election-win-rcna343690</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-chedrick-greene-mn-0840-09fa6b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Paul Sancya</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Chedrick Greene</media:text><media:description type="plain">Democrat Chedrick Greene defeated Republican Jason Tunney in a special election for a Michigan state Senate seat. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-michigan-jason-tunney-mn-0840-1481a0.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Paul Sancya</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Jason Tunney</media:text><media:description type="plain">Democrat Chedrick Greene defeated Republican Jason Tunney in a special election for a Michigan state Senate seat. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-chedrick-greene-mn-0840-09fa6b.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 02:51:49 GMT</pubDate><title>Democrats keep control of Michigan state Senate after special election win</title><updateDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 16:45:30 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Henry J. Gomez</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:54 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Businessman Vivek Ramaswamy has won Ohio’s Republican primary for governor, NBC News projects, advancing to what could be an expensive and competitive general election with Democrat Amy Acton in a state that has been brutal for Democrats in recent elections.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/vivek-ramaswamy-wins-gop-primary-governor-ohio-amy-acton-rcna343048</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/vivek-ramaswamy-wins-gop-primary-governor-ohio-amy-acton-rcna343048</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-vivek-ramaswamy-vsb-2014-edeb08.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Carolyn Kaster</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Vivek Ramaswamy</media:text><media:description type="plain">Republican Ohio gubernatorial candidate Vivek speaks during a watch party at the Spruce St. Sporting sports bar after winning the party&#39;s nomination for governor Tuesday, May 5, 2026, in Columbus.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-vivek-ramaswamy-vsb-2014-edeb08.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:54 GMT</pubDate><title>Vivek Ramaswamy wins GOP nomination for governor in Ohio</title><updateDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 00:20:30 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Henry J. Gomez</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Former Sen. Sherrod Brown has won the Democratic nomination in Ohio’s special Senate election, NBC News projects, paving the way for a nationally watched general election matchup against Republican incumbent Jon Husted</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/sherrod-brown-wins-ohio-senate-democratic-primary-jon-husted-rcna343049</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/sherrod-brown-wins-ohio-senate-democratic-primary-jon-husted-rcna343049</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-Sherrod-Brown-vsb-2025-19efa8.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Sue Ogrocki</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sherrod Brown</media:text><media:description type="plain">Democratic Ohio Senate candidate Sherrod Brown, a former three-term U.S. senator, speaks at a primary election night campaign event after winning the party&#39;s primary for US Senate in Cleveland, Tuesday, May 5, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-Sherrod-Brown-vsb-2025-19efa8.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</pubDate><title>Sherrod Brown wins Democratic Senate nomination in Ohio, setting up a key battleground race</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 23:38:01 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 06 May 2026 23:07:37 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>In our series “The Cost of Denial,” NBC News’ Erin McLaughlin reports on the problems facing military families with their he